description.narrative: By end 2021, DGAS, DGSELM, DSR, DS and health sector partners, including NGOs, in targeted zones have the capacity to prepare for and respond to health emergencies, which contributes to Child Health, Child Health (Covid), Health And Emergencies, Immunization, Maternal And Newborn Health, Polio Eradication. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Outcome 1. By the end of 2021, adolescents, pregnant and lactating women, mothers and children 0-5 years of age are using more quality health services in the 10 targeted provinces.

description.narrative: UNICEF provided technical and financial assistance in response to epidemics that occurred in 2019. In response to the measles epidemic, which originally started in April 2018, UNICEF supported organization of a response campaign in 10 districts in April 2019, in which 653,535 children were vaccinated, equivalent to 107.8 per cent administrative coverage and 90 per cent post survey coverage, and which contained the epidemic in these 10 districts. 467,455 children in 14 districts were vaccinated in December 2019, achieving 110 per cent administrative coverage. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:09/02/2020
